OL,3,CWhat is a 'council of sanctuary' and
OL,4,Cwhat does it mean?
OL,6,FA council of sanctuary is one which,
OL,7,Faccording to the City of Sanctuary
OL,8,FLocal Authority Network, is "committed
OL,9,Fto being welcoming and fair to
OL,10,Feveryone in the community."
OL,12,FCouncils which want to receive
OL,13,Fsanctuary status will usually agree to
OL,14,Fplans at a meeting, and publicly
OL,15,Fexpress its intention.
OL,17,FIt will then apply to the City of
OL,18,FSanctuary Local Authority Network,
OL,19,Fwhere a panel will decide whether to
OL,20,Faward the local authority with
OL,21,Fsanctuary status.
